It’s really true when they say every pregnancy is different. After two vaginal births, I thought this 3rd one would be a breeze. Nope! Boy was I wrong and in for a surprise. After 14 hours of being in labor with no success of dilating any further and a cord wrapped around his neck, we had to switch our birth plan to a c-section. So many thoughts and emotions ran through my head and I had to talk to myself internally to stay strong for my baby.
